of Mary Queen of Scots from the early modern period to today. The volume also includes the English translation of a widely circulated letter detailing the queen’s momentous execution. Made available to an English-speaking audience for the first time, this tragedy is the earliest dramatic reworking of the death of Mary Queen of Scots in a modern vernacular, spearheading a tradition that endures to this day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aDRAMA / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Italian studies.  aElizabeth I.  aElizabethan.  aFederico Della Valle.  aItalian literature.  aMary Queen of Scots.  aStuart.  aTudor.  abaroque.  acounter-reformation.  aearly modern history.  aearly modern theatre.  apolitics.1 aBattista, Fabio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079736740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754529140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487545291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487545291/original  a978-3-11-079736-7  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles